[4] Brampton, Canada
Date: Sat 17 Feb 2018
Source: Brampton Guardian [edited]
https://www.bramptonguardian.com/news-story/8140509-updated-health-warning-issued-after-brampton-infant-with-measles-travels-on-air-canada-flight-from-zurich-on-feb-12/


Peel Public Health confirmed a 2nd case of the measles in Brampton on Fri 16 Feb 2018, this time in an infant who recently travelled on a flight from Zurich, Switzerland on 12 Feb 2018.

In a release sent Fri 16 Feb 2018, health officials issued a warning and advisory to anyone travelling on an Air Canada flight from Switzerland on the morning of 12 Feb 2018 [see URL for flight details and other possible locations where exposure may have occurred].

Those who travelled on that flight are being advised by Peel Public Health to do the following:

- "Check your immunization records to make sure you and your children have had 2 doses of the measles vaccine (MMR or MMRV). Your child's immunization record (yellow card) or your doctor can provide this information. Two doses of measles vaccine are recommended for anyone born after 1969."

- "Watch for symptoms of measles for 21 days after exposure. These include a high fever; cold-like symptoms (cough/runny nose); sore eyes or sensitivity to light; small spots with a white centre on the inside of the mouth; and a red rash lasting 4-7 days."

This is the 2nd case of measles confirmed in Brampton in as many days. Peel Health officials confirmed a case in an adult yesterday [Fri 16 Feb 2018], also from Brampton. That person also recently travelled internationally, said officials.

"The virus can only live outside the body on surfaces and in the air for up to 2 hours, so people who visited these locations or used these services at other times are not at risk," Peel Public Health said in a statement.

Anyone who believes they or a family member may have been exposed in either case must call ahead to any medical facilities they plan to visit to alert them that they have come into contact with someone with the virus.

[Byline: Graeme Frisque]

