******
[5] Philippines
Date: 16 Feb 2018
Source: GMA News [edited]
http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/news/regions/643647/davao-city-still-in-middle-of-measles-outbreak/story/


The Davao City Health Office on Fri [16 Feb 2018] said the measles outbreak declared last 22 Jan 2018 has yet to be lifted, even as the number of people infected by the viral disease has gone down.

According to a News to Go report, the city health office confirmed 23 out of over 300 suspected cases of measles infection recorded since November 2017, saying it was still considered above the norm.

Earlier, as of last 6 Jan 2018, a total of 222 Davao City residents tested positive for measles. On Fri [16 Feb 2018], the health office said 18 infected people in the city have died.

Local health officials said the measles outbreak was not connected to the "Dengvaxia scare," which transpired after the government's nationwide anti-dengue program vaccinated over 800 000 children with Dengvaxia, a drug that was later warned to result in severe symptoms if administered to children who have not yet contracted the dengue virus.

The health office also noted that, due to the public's fear of being vaccinated, the city's immunization rate was low.

The report said the Department of Health, for its part, assured the public that the measles vaccine was tried and tested.

